subSubSection.paragraph:
Since 

Solanum

is such a large and diverse group, particularly in the Andes, it is not surprising that many new species and taxonomic difficulties remain. This is particularly true in undercollected areas of the Andes, but recently many inroads have been made (
Knapp 2010
; 
Stern and Bohs 2010
; 
Farruggia and Bohs 2010
; 
Tepe et al. 2012
; 

Saerkinen
et al. 2013

). Field collections, revisionary, and phylogenetic study have spurred the description of species that otherwise may remain as "herbarium names".
